FBIS3-8919 "dreeu052_k_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-052 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 CROATIA President Tudjman Leaves for Washington LD1703093394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 17 Mar 94 LD1703093394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman has left for Washington. This afternoon, Central European time, he is to have talks with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher. President Tudjman is also to open the Croatian Embassy in Washington today, about which THE WASHINGTON TIMES wrote yesterday. [passage omitted] President Tudjman and Alija Izetbegovic are to sign bases for a confederal agreement between the Republic of Croatia and the federal Bosnia-Herzegovina tomorrow. He is also to attend a ceremony at which an agreement on the establishment of a federation between the Croats and the Bosniak Muslims in Bosnia-Herzegovina will be signed. In Washington the Croatian president is also to meet President Clinton, representatives of the largest international financial organizations, journalists, and Croatian emigrants. In New York he is to meet United Nations Secretary General Butrus-Ghali. [passage omitted]
